[metadata]
Name:Chain Lightning copy chain (opponent pays RR)
Goal:Win
Turns:2
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 casts Chain Lightning ({R}) at Player 2. Chain Lightning "deals 3 damage to any target. Then that player or that permanent's controller may pay {R}{R}. If the player does, they may copy this spell and may choose a new target for that copy" (CR 707.10 + 601.2c). Player 2 HAS red mana (Mountains), so it pays {R}{R}, copies Chain Lightning, and retargets it at the original caster (Player 1) — the canonical "chain". The copy deals 3 to Player 1. The chain TERMINATES when a player runs out of untapped red to pay {R}{R} again (mana is actually deducted — mtg-152). This puzzle asserts the copy is created (the "copies Chain Lightning" gamelog) and that BOTH players take 3 damage (20 -> 17 each).

